items.title: Hello, and welcome to the study!
items.content:
In this task, you will need to use the z and m keys on the computer keyboard. Please locate these keys now.

When you begin the task, words and pictures will begin to flash up on the screen, one at a time. The goal of the task is to learn to press either the z or the m key depending on what picture/image appears on the screen, based on the feedback that the test provides you.

Try to respond AS QUICKLY AND AS ACCURATELY AS POSSIBLE.

items.title: Good!
items.content:
When you next click "Continue task", words and pictures will again begin to flash up on the screen, one at a time. As before, the goal of the task is to learn to press either the z or the m key depending on what picture/image appears on the screen, based on the feedback that the test provides you.

Try to respond AS QUICKLY AND AS ACCURATELY AS POSSIBLE.

When you're ready, click "Continue task" to begin.

items.title: You will first complete some practice trials.
items.content: This will help you to get acquainted with the test. When you're ready, click "Start practice" to begin.

items.title: Good!
items.content: You will now begin the main task. Remember: learn how to respond by pressing the <kbd>z</kbd> or the <kbd>m</kbd> key to each stimulus. When you're ready, click "Start task" to begin.

items.title: Thank you for your participation!
items.content: The task is now complete and your data have been saved. You may close this window.
